ROSS RIVER VIRUS - AUSTRALIA (NEW SOUTH WALES) (02)
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Ross River virus - Australia (New South Wales) 980109223432
[1
Date: Mon, 12 Jan 1998 11:44:55 -0800
From: Richard C. Russell <RichardR@cidm.wh.su.edu.au>

It is true there were 1,582 cases reported for NSW in 1997 (calendar year)
and 1,076 for 1996 - a substantial increase over the 242 reported in 1995 -
and the virus did 'reach' the outskirts of Sydney for the first time in any
substantial respect. However, the great majority of these cases in both
1996 and 1997 occurred in the months January through May, the usual
'transmission season' in NSW.
With respect to the current 'transmission season' for 1998, it is of course
too early for January reports, but there is no indication of any
exceptional activity in the late spring months; there were only 12 reports
for November 1997 and 10 for December 1997, compared with the 1996 figures
of 32 and 32 for the same months. Suffice to say, there is no sign of any
'alarming' activity in NSW this current season, at least not at this time.
--
